* The little kitten in Iron Raptors back compartment squeeked in protest. It 
was not used to being bounced around in a small box. It tried rightening 
itself on what it thought was the floor, but Iron Raptor kept moving around 
so much that he couldn't tell which surface was the floor and which wasn't. 
When she moved next he fell on his side, making him squeek a quick, load 
squeek. He shook his little head and tried again, only to get his head 
rammed into a wall. his head wobbled to and fro. He shook his head and 
sighed. He placed his head on his paws and was going to go to sleep when he 
was tossed onto his back. His legs kicking and struggling to righten him. He 
growled. This was going to be a long journey.....*
